uk.co.saiman.experiment.sample

Interface SampleExperimentType<T extends SampleConfiguration>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of sample configuration for the instrument
    All Superinterfaces:
    ExperimentType<T>, uk.co.strangeskies.reflection.Reified
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RadialStageExperimentType<T>, XYStageExperimentType<T>

    public interface SampleExperimentType<T extends SampleConfiguration>
extends ExperimentType<T>
    Configure the sample position to perform an experiment at. Typically most other experiment nodes will be descendant to a sample experiment node, such that they operate on the configured sample.

        Description copied from interface: ExperimentType
        Test whether a node of the given type may follow from the given node and be validly added as its child. The penultimate descendant node should be a descendant of a node of this type.

        This test is performed on all ancestors when an attempt is made to add a new node.
